This paper is about improving the efficiency and accuracy of text recognition in images using convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on the DenseNet architecture and proposes a new convolutional block called Fast Dense Block (FDB) to reduce the computational cost of the network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a fast network of DenseNet to improve text recognition performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
